headline: Better Semiconductor Stock: AMD vs. Broadcom
summary: The past year has been a solid one for semiconductor companies, as evident from the 21% gains clocked by the PHLX Semiconductor Sector index during this period.  For instance, while shares of Broadcom (NASDAQ: AVGO) have jumped an impressive 115% in the past year, Advanced Micro Devices (NASDAQ: AMD) stock has headed in the opposite direction and lost 14% of its value.  Both companies play a key role in the semiconductor market as they design chips that are used in personal computers (PCs), smartphones, gaming consoles, and data centers.
